Context: This workshop is being offered at George Brown College to help students prepare for job interviews. The workshop will cover the purpose of interviews, different types of interview questions, effective answering techniques, and preparation tips. Interested students are encouraged to register early as seats are limited and can do so through the GBCareers portal. Additional information, including application deadlines and college news, can be obtained by signing up for updates on the website. The contact details for enquiries are 416-415-2000 and TTY: 1-877-515-5559, with emails directed to ask.george@georgebrown.ca. It is important to note that the information on the website may be subject to change without notice, and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
